7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 381, L.D. 613, “An Act to Amend the
10 Maine Death with Dignity Act to Ensure Access by Qualified Patients”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §2140, sub-§11, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 271, §4, is repealed
13 and the following enacted in its place:
14 11. Written and oral requests; waiting periods. To receive a prescription for
15 medication that the qualified patient may self-administer under this Act, a qualified patient
16 must make 2 oral requests, at least 15 days apart, and a written request to the qualified
17 patient's attending physician. At the time the qualified patient makes the qualified patient's
18 2nd oral request, the attending physician shall offer the qualified patient an opportunity to
19 rescind the request. The date the qualified patient signs the written request must be no
20 earlier than 15 days after the initial oral request. At least 48 hours must elapse between the
21 date the qualified patient signs the written request and the writing of a prescription under
22 this Act.
23 The attending physician may waive any portion or all of the waiting periods required in
24 this subsection if, in the attending physician's medical opinion, it is in the best interests of
25 the qualified patient, given the qualified patient's condition.
26 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §2140, sub-§13, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 271, §4, is repealed.'
27 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 4 and inserting the following:
28 'Sec. 4. 22 MRSA §2140, sub-§14, ¶H is enacted to read:
29 H. When a portion or all of the waiting periods under this section have been waived
30 pursuant to subsection 11, a note by the attending physician that, in the attending
31 physician's medical opinion, it is in the best interests of the qualified patient to waive
32 a portion or all of the waiting periods, given the qualified patient's condition, and what
33 portion of the waiting periods has been waived.'
34 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
35 number to read consecutively.
